{
  "video_id": "d-8n24ZwZcQ",
  "title": "We need nuclear power to solve climate change | Joe Lassiter",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12980.0,
      "end_time": 15452.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s easy to forget that last night,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16203.0,
      "end_time": 19682.0,
      "text": "one billion people went to sleep without access to electricity."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 20940.0,
      "end_time": 21424.0,
      "text": "One billion people."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22298.0,
      "end_time": 27370.0,
      "text": "Two and a half billion people did not have access to clean cooking fuels"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 27553.0,
      "end_time": 28885.0,
      "text": "or clean heating fuels."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 30234.0,
      "end_time": 32596.0,
      "text": "Those are the problems in the developing world."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 32982.0,
      "end_time": 35618.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s easy for us not to be empathetic"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35642.0,
      "end_time": 37955.0,
      "text": "with those people who seem so distanced from us."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 38331.0,
      "end_time": 41106.0,
      "text": "But even in our own world, the developed world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 41725.0,
      "end_time": 44630.0,
      "text": "we see the tension of stagnant economies"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 45234.0,
      "end_time": 47849.0,
      "text": "impacting the lives of people around us."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 48241.0,
      "end_time": 51345.0,
      "text": "We see it in whole pieces of the economy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 51813.0,
      "end_time": 54912.0,
      "text": "where the people involved have lost hope about the future"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 55220.0,
      "end_time": 56942.0,
      "text": "and despair about the present."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 57457.0,
      "end_time": 59500.0,
      "text": "We see that in the Brexit vote."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 59546.0,
      "end_time": 62985.0,
      "text": "We see that in the Sanders/Trump campaigns in my own country."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 63667.0,
      "end_time": 68195.0,
      "text": "But even in countries as recently turning the corner"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 68619.0,
      "end_time": 70439.0,
      "text": "towards being in the developed world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 70463.0,
      "end_time": 71702.0,
      "text": "in China,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 71727.0,
      "end_time": 74303.0,
      "text": "we see the difficulty that President Xi has"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 74700.0,
      "end_time": 79666.0,
      "text": "as he begins to un-employ so many people in his coal and mining industries"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 80214.0,
      "end_time": 82145.0,
      "text": "who see no future for themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 83183.0,
      "end_time": 86186.0,
      "text": "As we as a society figure out how to manage"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 86210.0,
      "end_time": 88163.0,
      "text": "the problems of the developed world"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 88187.0,
      "end_time": 90235.0,
      "text": "and the problems of the developing world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 90259.0,
      "end_time": 93107.0,
      "text": "we have to look at how we move forward"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 93131.0,
      "end_time": 96841.0,
      "text": "and manage the environmental impact of those decisions."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 97868.0,
      "end_time": 100967.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve been working on this problem for 25 years, since Rio,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 100991.0,
      "end_time": 102674.0,
      "text": "the Kyoto Protocols."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 103223.0,
      "end_time": 105797.0,
      "text": "Our most recent move is the Paris treaty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 106514.0,
      "end_time": 109880.0,
      "text": "and the resulting climate agreements"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 109112.0,
      "end_time": 112210.0,
      "text": "that are being ratified by nations around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 112450.0,
      "end_time": 114232.0,
      "text": "I think we can be very hopeful"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 114256.0,
      "end_time": 117394.0,
      "text": "that those agreements, which are bottom-up agreements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 117418.0,
      "end_time": 120279.0,
      "text": "where nations have said what they think they can do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 120303.0,
      "end_time": 124381.0,
      "text": "are genuine and forthcoming for the vast majority of the parties."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 124977.0,
      "end_time": 126545.0,
      "text": "The unfortunate thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 127205.0,
      "end_time": 130732.0,
      "text": "is that now, as we look at the independent analyses"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 130756.0,
      "end_time": 133955.0,
      "text": "of what those climate treaties are liable to yield,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 135830.0,
      "end_time": 137992.0,
      "text": "the magnitude of the problem before us becomes clear."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 138965.0,
      "end_time": 143380.0,
      "text": "This is the United States Energy Information Agency&#39;s assessment"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 143625.0,
      "end_time": 148313.0,
      "text": "of what will happen if the countries implement the climate commitments"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 148337.0,
      "end_time": 150373.0,
      "text": "that they&#39;ve made in Paris"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 150397.0,
      "end_time": 152347.0,
      "text": "between now and 2040."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 153221.0,
      "end_time": 157441.0,
      "text": "It shows basically CO2 emissions around the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 157465.0,
      "end_time": 159146.0,
      "text": "over the next 30 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 160236.0,
      "end_time": 163751.0,
      "text": "There are three things that you need to look at and appreciate."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 164177.0,
      "end_time": 168347.0,
      "text": "One, CO2 emissions are expected to continue to grow"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 168372.0,
      "end_time": 169831.0,
      "text": "for the next 30 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 171265.0,
      "end_time": 173530.0,
      "text": "In order to control climate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 174540.0,
      "end_time": 177400.0,
      "text": "CO2 emissions have to literally go to zero"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 177564.0,
      "end_time": 181718.0,
      "text": "because it&#39;s the cumulative emissions that drive heating on the planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 182445.0,
      "end_time": 186560.0,
      "text": "This should tell you that we are losing the race to fossil fuels."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 187567.0,
      "end_time": 189430.0,
      "text": "The second thing you should notice"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 189454.0,
      "end_time": 193747.0,
      "text": "is that the bulk of the growth comes from the developing countries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 193771.0,
      "end_time": 196835.0,
      "text": "from China, from India, from the rest of the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 196860.0,
      "end_time": 200990.0,
      "text": "which includes South Africa and Indonesia and Brazil,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 201240.0,
      "end_time": 203853.0,
      "text": "as most of these countries move their people"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 204353.0,
      "end_time": 207264.0,
      "text": "into the lower range of lifestyles"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 207288.0,
      "end_time": 211540.0,
      "text": "that we literally take for granted in the developed world."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 212495.0,
      "end_time": 214878.0,
      "text": "The final thing that you should notice"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 214902.0,
      "end_time": 216560.0,
      "text": "is that each year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 217394.0,
      "end_time": 224354.0,
      "text": "about 10 gigatons of carbon are getting added to the planet&#39;s atmosphere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 224994.0,
      "end_time": 227626.0,
      "text": "and then diffusing into the ocean and into the land."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 228110.0,
      "end_time": 233321.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s on top of the 550 gigatons that are in place today."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 234620.0,
      "end_time": 235896.0,
      "text": "At the end of 30 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 235920.0,
      "end_time": 240472.0,
      "text": "we will have put 850 gigatons of carbon into the air,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 241171.0,
      "end_time": 243422.0,
      "text": "and that probably goes a long way"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 243446.0,
      "end_time": 249607.0,
      "text": "towards locking in a 2-4 degree C increase in global mean surface temperatures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 250140.0,
      "end_time": 252826.0,
      "text": "locking in ocean acidification"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 253227.0,
      "end_time": 255204.0,
      "text": "and locking in sea level rise."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 256379.00000000003,
      "end_time": 259205.00000000003,
      "text": "Now, this is a projection made by men"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 260197.0,
      "end_time": 262125.0,
      "text": "by the actions of society,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 262863.0,
      "end_time": 265339.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s ours to change, not to accept."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 265912.0,
      "end_time": 269789.0,
      "text": "But the magnitude of the problem is something we need to appreciate."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 270648.0,
      "end_time": 273910.0,
      "text": "Different nations make different energy choices."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 273115.0,
      "end_time": 275442.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a function of their natural resources."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 275466.0,
      "end_time": 277475.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a function of their climate."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 277499.0,
      "end_time": 281981.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a function of the development path that they&#39;ve followed as a society."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 282664.0,
      "end_time": 286167.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a function of where on the surface of the planet they are."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 286191.0,
      "end_time": 288691.0,
      "text": "Are they where it&#39;s dark a lot of the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 288715.0,
      "end_time": 290575.0,
      "text": "or are they at the mid-latitudes?"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 290989.0,
      "end_time": 294707.0,
      "text": "Many, many, many things go into the choices of countries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 295185.0,
      "end_time": 297362.0,
      "text": "and they each make a different choice."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 298878.0,
      "end_time": 302390.0,
      "text": "The overwhelming thing that we need to appreciate"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 302640.0,
      "end_time": 303981.0,
      "text": "is the choice that China has made."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 304695.0,
      "end_time": 307289.0,
      "text": "China has made the choice,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 307313.0,
      "end_time": 309818.0,
      "text": "and will make the choice, to run on coal."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 310358.0,
      "end_time": 312377.0,
      "text": "The United States has an alternative."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 312401.0,
      "end_time": 314158.0,
      "text": "It can run on natural gas"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 314182.0,
      "end_time": 318700.0,
      "text": "as a result of the inventions of fracking and shale gas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 318310.0,
      "end_time": 319502.0,
      "text": "which we have here."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 319526.0,
      "end_time": 321910.0,
      "text": "They provide an alternative."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 322662.0,
      "end_time": 325373.0,
      "text": "The OECD Europe has a choice."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 325881.0,
      "end_time": 328950.0,
      "text": "It has renewables that it can afford to deploy in Germany"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 328974.0,
      "end_time": 331591.0,
      "text": "because it&#39;s rich enough to afford to do it."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 331615.0,
      "end_time": 337103.0,
      "text": "The French and the British show interest in nuclear power."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 337702.0,
      "end_time": 342307.0,
      "text": "Eastern Europe, still very heavily committed to natural gas and to coal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 342331.0,
      "end_time": 345590.0,
      "text": "and with natural gas that comes from Russia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 345830.0,
      "end_time": 346853.0,
      "text": "with all of its entanglements."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 347558.0,
      "end_time": 350150.0,
      "text": "China has many fewer choices"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 350390.0,
      "end_time": 352289.0,
      "text": "and a much harder row to hoe."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 353557.0,
      "end_time": 356589.0,
      "text": "If you look at China, and you ask yourself"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 356613.0,
      "end_time": 358817.0,
      "text": "why has coal been important to it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 358841.0,
      "end_time": 361530.0,
      "text": "you have to remember what China&#39;s done."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 361534.0,
      "end_time": 364841.0,
      "text": "China brought people to power, not power to people."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 365380.0,
      "end_time": 367830.0,
      "text": "It didn&#39;t do rural electrification."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 368427.0,
      "end_time": 369601.0,
      "text": "It urbanized."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 369954.0,
      "end_time": 374158.0,
      "text": "It urbanized by taking low-cost labor and low-cost energy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 374182.0,
      "end_time": 376990.0,
      "text": "creating export industries"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 376123.0,
      "end_time": 378630.0,
      "text": "that could fund a tremendous amount of growth."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 379535.0,
      "end_time": 381739.0,
      "text": "If we look at China&#39;s path,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 381763.0,
      "end_time": 385895.0,
      "text": "all of us know that prosperity in China has dramatically increased."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 386713.0,
      "end_time": 391259.0,
      "text": "In 1980, 80 percent of China&#39;s population"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 391283.0,
      "end_time": 393717.0,
      "text": "lived below the extreme poverty level,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 394493.0,
      "end_time": 398253.0,
      "text": "below the level of having $1.90 per person per day."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 398658.0,
      "end_time": 404130.0,
      "text": "By the year 2000, only 20 percent of China&#39;s population"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 404154.0,
      "end_time": 406688.0,
      "text": "lived below the extreme poverty level --"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 407498.0,
      "end_time": 409192.0,
      "text": "a remarkable feat,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 409977.0,
      "end_time": 412344.0,
      "text": "admittedly, with some costs in civil liberties"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 412368.0,
      "end_time": 415324.0,
      "text": "that would be tough to accept in the Western world."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 416548.0,
      "end_time": 419455.0,
      "text": "But the impact of all that wealth"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 419479.0,
      "end_time": 422991.0,
      "text": "allowed people to get massively better nutrition."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 423484.0,
      "end_time": 426198.0,
      "text": "It allowed water pipes to be placed."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 426223.0,
      "end_time": 428682.0,
      "text": "It allowed sewage pipes to be placed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 428706.0,
      "end_time": 431678.0,
      "text": "dramatic decrease in diarrheal diseases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 432590.0,
      "end_time": 435212.0,
      "text": "at the cost of some outdoor air pollution."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 436700.0,
      "end_time": 438349.0,
      "text": "But in 1980, and even today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 438374.0,
      "end_time": 442381.0,
      "text": "the number one killer in China is indoor air pollution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 442833.0,
      "end_time": 447602.0,
      "text": "because people do not have access to clean cooking and heating fuels."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 448660.0,
      "end_time": 450174.0,
      "text": "In fact, in 2040,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 451794.0,
      "end_time": 456568.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s still estimated that 200 million people in China"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 456593.0,
      "end_time": 460144.0,
      "text": "will not have access to clean cooking fuels."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 461133.0,
      "end_time": 463489.0,
      "text": "They have a remarkable path to follow."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 464854.0,
      "end_time": 469602.0,
      "text": "India also needs to meet the needs of its own people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 469626.0,
      "end_time": 471799.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s going to do that by burning coal."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 472475.0,
      "end_time": 477953.0,
      "text": "When we look at the EIA&#39;s projections of coal burning in India,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 478591.0,
      "end_time": 483494.0,
      "text": "India will supply nearly four times as much of its energy from coal"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 483518.0,
      "end_time": 485556.0,
      "text": "as it will from renewables."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 486962.0,
      "end_time": 489815.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not because they don&#39;t know the alternatives;"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 489839.0,
      "end_time": 493584.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s because rich countries can do what they choose,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 494162.0,
      "end_time": 496308.0,
      "text": "poor countries do what they must."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 498198.0,
      "end_time": 501883.0,
      "text": "So what can we do to stop coal&#39;s emissions in time?"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 502899.0,
      "end_time": 507511.0,
      "text": "What can we do that changes this forecast that&#39;s in front of us?"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 507535.0,
      "end_time": 511602.0,
      "text": "Because it&#39;s a forecast that we can change if we have the will to do it."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 513940.00000000006,
      "end_time": 516513.00000000006,
      "text": "First of all, we have to think about the magnitude of the problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 516537.00000000006,
      "end_time": 518581.00000000006,
      "text": "Between now and 2040,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 519104.00000000006,
      "end_time": 524847.0,
      "text": "800 to 1,600 new coal plants are going to be built around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 526850.0,
      "end_time": 530694.0,
      "text": "This week, between one and three one-gigawatt coal plants"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 530718.0,
      "end_time": 532929.0,
      "text": "are being turned on around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 533817.0,
      "end_time": 537867.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s happening regardless of what we want,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 537891.0,
      "end_time": 540399.0,
      "text": "because the people that rule their countries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 540423.0,
      "end_time": 542793.0,
      "text": "assessing the interests of their citizens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 542817.0,
      "end_time": 546232.0,
      "text": "have decided it&#39;s in the interest of their citizens to do that."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 547335.0,
      "end_time": 551302.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s going to happen unless they have a better alternative."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 551726.0,
      "end_time": 555483.0,
      "text": "And every 100 of those plants will use up"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 555507.0,
      "end_time": 558637.0,
      "text": "between one percent and three percent"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 558662.0,
      "end_time": 560280.0,
      "text": "of the Earth&#39;s climate budget."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 561264.0,
      "end_time": 564755.0,
      "text": "So every day that you go home thinking that you should do something"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 564779.0,
      "end_time": 566550.0,
      "text": "about global warming,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 566594.0,
      "end_time": 568526.0,
      "text": "at the end of that week, remember:"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 568550.0,
      "end_time": 572943.0,
      "text": "somebody fired up a coal plant that&#39;s going to run for 50 years"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 572967.0,
      "end_time": 576430.0,
      "text": "and take away your ability to change it."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 577972.0,
      "end_time": 581566.0,
      "text": "What we&#39;ve forgotten is something that Vinod Khosla used to talk about,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 581590.0,
      "end_time": 584712.0,
      "text": "a man of Indian ethnicity but an American venture capitalist."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 585339.0,
      "end_time": 588164.0,
      "text": "And he said, back in the early 2000s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 588188.0,
      "end_time": 592194.0,
      "text": "that if you needed to get China and India off of fossil fuels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 592219.0,
      "end_time": 595815.0,
      "text": "you had to create a technology that passed the \"Chindia test,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 596640.0,
      "end_time": 599980.0,
      "text": "\"Chindia\" being the appending of the two words."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 599900.0,
      "end_time": 602259.0,
      "text": "It had to be first of all viable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 602283.0,
      "end_time": 605877.0,
      "text": "meaning that technically, they could implement it in their country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 605901.0,
      "end_time": 608905.0,
      "text": "and that it would be accepted by the people in the country."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 610191.0,
      "end_time": 616764.0,
      "text": "Two, it had to be a technology that was scalable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 616788.0,
      "end_time": 619806.0,
      "text": "that it could deliver the same benefits"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 619830.0,
      "end_time": 622907.0,
      "text": "on the same timetable as fossil fuels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 623387.0,
      "end_time": 627179.0,
      "text": "so that they can enjoy the kind of life, again, that we take for granted."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 627766.0,
      "end_time": 630275.0,
      "text": "And third, it had to be cost-effective"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 630299.0,
      "end_time": 632985.0,
      "text": "without subsidy or without mandate."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 633432.0,
      "end_time": 636146.0,
      "text": "It had to stand on its own two feet;"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 636170.0,
      "end_time": 640490.0,
      "text": "it could not be maintained for that many people"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 640730.0,
      "end_time": 642529.0,
      "text": "if in fact, those countries had to go begging"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 643900.0,
      "end_time": 646828.0,
      "text": "or had some foreign country say, \"I won&#39;t trade with you,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 647328.0,
      "end_time": 650611.0,
      "text": "in order to get the technology shift to occur."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 652168.0,
      "end_time": 653854.0,
      "text": "If you look at the Chindia test,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 653878.0,
      "end_time": 658503.0,
      "text": "we simply have not come up with alternatives that meet that test."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 658984.0,
      "end_time": 661828.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s what the EIA forecast tells us."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 662765.0,
      "end_time": 666115.0,
      "text": "China&#39;s building 800 gigawatts of coal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 666866.0,
      "end_time": 669500.0,
      "text": "400 gigawatts of hydro,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 669772.0,
      "end_time": 672144.0,
      "text": "about 200 gigawatts of nuclear,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 672501.0,
      "end_time": 676562.0,
      "text": "and on an energy-equivalent basis, adjusting for intermittency,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 676586.0,
      "end_time": 678877.0,
      "text": "about 100 gigawatts of renewables."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 679554.0,
      "end_time": 681462.0,
      "text": "800 gigawatts of coal."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 681805.0,
      "end_time": 685357.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re doing that, knowing the costs better than any other country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 685381.0,
      "end_time": 687933.0,
      "text": "knowing the need better than any other country."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 688454.0,
      "end_time": 691800.0,
      "text": "But that&#39;s what they&#39;re aiming for in 2040"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 691105.0,
      "end_time": 693429.0,
      "text": "unless we give them a better choice."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 694199.0,
      "end_time": 695639.0,
      "text": "To give them a better choice,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 695663.0,
      "end_time": 698224.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s going to have to meet the Chindia test."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 698248.0,
      "end_time": 700906.0,
      "text": "If you look at all the alternatives that are out there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 700930.0,
      "end_time": 703430.0,
      "text": "there are really two that come near to meeting it."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 703865.0,
      "end_time": 707750.0,
      "text": "First is this area of new nuclear that I&#39;ll talk about in just a second."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 708107.0,
      "end_time": 711406.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a new generation of nuclear plants that are on the drawing boards"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 711431.0,
      "end_time": 712707.0,
      "text": "around the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 712731.0,
      "end_time": 715690.0,
      "text": "and the people who are developing these say"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 715930.0,
      "end_time": 718634.0,
      "text": "we can get them in position to demo by 2025"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 719252.0,
      "end_time": 722525.0,
      "text": "and to scale by 2030, if you will just let us."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 723246.0,
      "end_time": 726790.0,
      "text": "The second alternative that could be there in time"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 726771.0,
      "end_time": 730476.0,
      "text": "is utility-scale solar backed up with natural gas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 730500.0,
      "end_time": 732224.0,
      "text": "which we can use today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 732248.0,
      "end_time": 735182.0,
      "text": "versus the batteries which are still under development."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 736589.0,
      "end_time": 738924.0,
      "text": "So what&#39;s holding new nuclear back?"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 739686.0,
      "end_time": 743361.0,
      "text": "Outdated regulations and yesterday&#39;s mindsets."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 743972.0,
      "end_time": 748167.0,
      "text": "We have not used our latest scientific thinking on radiological health"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 748191.0,
      "end_time": 750879.0,
      "text": "to think how we communicate with the public"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 750903.0,
      "end_time": 753281.0,
      "text": "and govern the testing of new nuclear reactors."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 753729.0,
      "end_time": 757926.0,
      "text": "We have new scientific knowledge that we need to use"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 757950.0,
      "end_time": 762489.0,
      "text": "in order to improve the way we regulate nuclear industry."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 762872.0,
      "end_time": 765320.0,
      "text": "The second thing is we&#39;ve got a mindset"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 765345.0,
      "end_time": 768154.0,
      "text": "that it takes 25 years and 2 to 5 billion dollars"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 768178.0,
      "end_time": 769913.0,
      "text": "to develop a nuclear power plant."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 769937.0,
      "end_time": 773866.0,
      "text": "That comes from the historical, military mindset"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 774443.0,
      "end_time": 776851.0,
      "text": "of the places nuclear power came from."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 777356.0,
      "end_time": 779567.0,
      "text": "These new nuclear ventures are saying"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 779591.0,
      "end_time": 782496.0,
      "text": "that they can deliver power for 5 cents a kilowatt hour;"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 783212.0,
      "end_time": 785813.0,
      "text": "they can deliver it for 100 gigawatts a year;"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 786543.0,
      "end_time": 788772.0,
      "text": "they can demo it by 2025;"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 789168.0,
      "end_time": 792173.0,
      "text": "and they can deliver it in scale by 2030,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 792634.0,
      "end_time": 794833.0,
      "text": "if only we give them a chance."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 796640.0,
      "end_time": 798967.0,
      "text": "Right now, we&#39;re basically waiting for a miracle."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 799888.0,
      "end_time": 801472.0,
      "text": "What we need is a choice."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 801952.0,
      "end_time": 804756.0,
      "text": "If they can&#39;t make it safe, if they can&#39;t make it cheap,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 804780.0,
      "end_time": 806597.0,
      "text": "it should not be deployed."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 806621.0,
      "end_time": 810675.0,
      "text": "But what I want you to do is not carry an idea forward,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 810699.0,
      "end_time": 812349.0,
      "text": "but write your leaders,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 812374.0,
      "end_time": 814752.0,
      "text": "write the head of the NGOs you support,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 814776.0,
      "end_time": 817718.0,
      "text": "and tell them to give you the choice,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 818290.0,
      "end_time": 819440.0,
      "text": "not the past."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 819465.0,
      "end_time": 820649.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 820673.0,
      "end_time": 825465.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}